---
import Navigation from '../components/Navigation.astro';
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>About William | William64.com</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Learn more about William Sutton - software engineer, systems thinker, and retro computing enthusiast." />
    
    <!-- Strategic Preloading -->
    <link rel="preload" href="/styles.css" as="style">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css" />
  </head>
  <body class="bg-black text-green-400 font-mono">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-6">
      <header class="border-b border-green-700 pb-4 mb-8">
        <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold mb-2">William64.com</h1>
        <Navigation />
      </header>
      
      <main>
        <h1 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-6">About Me</h1>
        
        <section class="mb-10">
          <div class="terminal-window p-3 sm:p-4 bg-black border border-green-700 mb-6">
            <pre class="text-sm mb-2">$ whoami</pre>
            <pre class="terminal-output">William Sutton</pre>
            <pre class="text-sm mb-2">$ cat /etc/profile</pre>
            <pre class="terminal-output">Self-taught software engineer with a passion for 
understanding systems from first principles.</pre>
          </div>
          
          <p class="mb-4">
            I'm William, a software engineer whose journey began with an early fascination with how software works under the hood. 
            My passion for programming was ignited when my brother introduced me to a Visual Basic decompiler—seeing code that I 
            couldn't understand drove me to learn how to write it properly myself.
          </p>
          
          <p class="mb-4">
            I believe in approaching technology with curiosity and a determination to understand the fundamentals. This philosophy has 
            guided my self-directed learning path from Visual Basic to C++ and beyond.
          </p>
        </section>
        
        <section class="mb-10">
          <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl border-b border-green-700 pb-2 mb-4">Technical Journey</h2>
          
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 sm:gap-6">
            <div class="terminal-window p-3 sm:p-4 bg-black border border-green-700">
              <pre class="text-sm mb-2">$ ls ~/skills/languages</pre>
              <pre class="terminal-output">Visual Basic
HTML/CSS
C++
OpenGL
Various web technologies</pre>
            </div>
            
            <div class="terminal-window p-3 sm:p-4 bg-black border border-green-700">
              <pre class="text-sm mb-2">$ ls ~/skills/learning_path</pre>
              <pre class="terminal-output">Self-taught programming
Online resources
3DBuzz tutorials
Open source contributions
Documentation improvements</pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>
        
        <section class="mb-10">
          <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl border-b border-green-700 pb-2 mb-4">My Journey</h2>
          
          <div class="terminal-window p-3 sm:p-4 bg-black border border-green-700 mb-6">
            <pre class="text-sm mb-2">$ git log --reverse --format="%an: %s"</pre>
            <pre class="terminal-output">William: Started with Visual Basic after seeing decompiled code
William: Learned HTML building websites on Angelfire and Geocities
William: Developed web forum for online gaming community
William: Mastered C++, OpenGL and 3D modeling via 3DBuzz tutorials
William: Contributed to otserv (Tibia server emulator)
William: Created documentation fixes for various open source projects
William: Launched William64.com as a project showcase</pre>
          </div>
          
          <p class="mb-4">
            My programming education has been entirely self-directed. A pivotal moment was investing in a 3DBuzz DVD 
            course that taught me C++, OpenGL, and 3D modeling—the best $80 I've spent on my technical education. 
            This hands-on approach to learning has shaped how I tackle problems and build solutions.
          </p>
          
          <p class="mb-4">
            I've contributed to the open-source community through code contributions to otserv (an open-source Tibia server emulator) 
            and by improving documentation across various projects. I believe strongly in the value of clear documentation and 
            take pride in making software more accessible to others.
          </p>
        </section>
        
        <section class="mb-10">
          <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl border-b border-green-700 pb-2 mb-4">Current Focus</h2>
          
          <p class="mb-4">
            William64.com represents my latest project—a platform to showcase my work and ongoing projects. 
            I'm constantly exploring new technologies and looking for interesting problems to solve.
          </p>
          
          <p class="mb-4">
            When I'm not coding, you might find me:
          </p>
          
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 pl-4">
            <li class="mb-2">Exploring new programming languages and frameworks</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Contributing to open source projects</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Optimizing and improving existing systems</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Researching best practices in software development</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
        
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl border-b border-green-700 pb-2 mb-4">Get in Touch</h2>
          
          <div class="terminal-window p-3 sm:p-4 bg-black border border-green-700 mb-6">
            <pre class="text-sm mb-2">$ finger william</pre>
            <pre class="terminal-output">Email: suttonwilliamd@gmail.com
GitHub: github.com/suttonwilliamd
</pre>
          </div>
          
          <p class="mb-4">
            I'm always interested in discussing technical challenges, collaboration opportunities, 
            or just connecting with fellow developers. Feel free to reach out through any of the channels above.
          </p>
        </section>
      </main>
      
      <footer class="mt-16 border-t border-green-700 pt-4 text-sm text-green-600">
        <p>&copy; 2025 William64. Built with Astro & hand-tuned HTML.</p>
      </footer>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  .terminal-window {
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  
  .terminal-output {
    color: #00ff99;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }
  
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    html {
      font-size: 14px;
    }
    
    .terminal-window {
      padding: 0.75rem;
    }
    
    .terminal-output {
      font-size: 0.9rem;
    }
  }
</style>
